<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="490" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,726,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Measurements (mm). 
<typeStatus box="[399,503,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Holotype</typeStatus>
male: Total length 22.0, length of pronotum 
<number box="[1015,1052,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="4.5">4.5</number>
, width of pronotum 
<number box="[1284,1322,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="5.5">5.5</number>
, length of tegmen 20.0, width of tegmen 
<number box="[494,532,762,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="5.5">5.5</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,726,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
General coloration glossy brown. Head yellowish light-brown, vertex and interocular space covered with black spots; ocelli orangish; frons yellowish with two symmetrical parallel dark-brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1219,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[249,1335,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[239,1348,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Epilampra pereirae sp. nov. Holotype ♂. 9. Head, ventral view. 10. Pronotum, dorsal view. 11. Supranal plate, dorsal view. 12. Subgenital plate, ventral view. 13. Left phallomere, dorsal view. 14. Median sclerite, dorsal view. 15. Detail median sclerite, dorsal view. 16. Right phallomere, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226106/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[1203,1219,835,859]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antennae brown, golden-tomentose. Pronotum grayish brown, entirely covered with dark brown dots (
<figureCitation box="[1130,1217,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[249,1335,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[239,1348,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Epilampra pereirae sp. nov. Holotype ♂. 9. Head, ventral view. 10. Pronotum, dorsal view. 11. Supranal plate, dorsal view. 12. Subgenital plate, ventral view. 13. Left phallomere, dorsal view. 14. Median sclerite, dorsal view. 15. Detail median sclerite, dorsal view. 16. Right phallomere, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226106/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[1186,1217,871,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs brown with whitish pulvilli. Tegmina brown, with marginal and scapular field bearing distinct dark brown dots, becoming lighter in discoidal and anal fields.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,726,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Head subtriangular, vertex slightly exposed under pronotum in dorsal view; interocular space wide, measuring about half distance between bases of antennal sockets; ocelli large and deflected. Antennae long, tomentose, extending past apex of abdomen; maxillar palpi tomentose, with apical segment dilated and larger than others.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,726,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Pronotum transverse, convex with two grooves diverging posterolaterally from the base, edges deflected, with rounded contour; base angular and sinuous. Legs spiny. Anteroventral margin of cephalic femur with five wellspaced robust spines extending to middle, followed by a row of 
<number box="[863,891,1159,1183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="12.0">12</number>
minute spines extending to apex plus two robust apical spines (
<typeStatus box="[313,371,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Type</typeStatus>
B 
<number box="[400,416,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="2.0">2</number>
); posteroventral margin with three robust spines, one in middle region, one next to basal third, and one apical; middle and posterior femora each with ventral margins bearing four robust and well-spaced spines, one of which is apical; genicular spine present; pulvilli present on all tarsomeres; arolium present, claws symmetrical and ventrally serrated. Tegmina long, reaching past apex of cerci; marginal field short, narrow and deflected; scapular field long and narrow, veins arranged obliquely; discoidal field ample, veins arranged longitudinally; anal field ample, with 
<number box="[584,612,1375,1399]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="12.0">12</number>
or more axillary veins. Wings developed, apical triangle present; costal sector with apex of branches of radial vein not dilated; anal field folded in a fan.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,726,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Abdominal supranal plate with slight median indentation between the cerci, which are short, bristly and widened (
<figureCitation box="[263,347,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[249,1335,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[239,1348,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Epilampra pereirae sp. nov. Holotype ♂. 9. Head, ventral view. 10. Pronotum, dorsal view. 11. Supranal plate, dorsal view. 12. Subgenital plate, ventral view. 13. Left phallomere, dorsal view. 14. Median sclerite, dorsal view. 15. Detail median sclerite, dorsal view. 16. Right phallomere, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226106/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[318,347,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate asymmetrical, pointed styles placed laterally to apex of plate (
<figureCitation box="[1281,1366,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[249,1335,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[239,1348,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Epilampra pereirae sp. nov. Holotype ♂. 9. Head, ventral view. 10. Pronotum, dorsal view. 11. Supranal plate, dorsal view. 12. Subgenital plate, ventral view. 13. Left phallomere, dorsal view. 14. Median sclerite, dorsal view. 15. Detail median sclerite, dorsal view. 16. Right phallomere, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226106/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[1335,1366,1483,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Left phallomere slightly developed, shaped as an inverted 
<collectingCountry box="[756,776,1519,1542]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">Y</collectingCountry>
, with two projections, one of which is strongly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[249,1335,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[239,1348,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Epilampra pereirae sp. nov. Holotype ♂. 9. Head, ventral view. 10. Pronotum, dorsal view. 11. Supranal plate, dorsal view. 12. Subgenital plate, ventral view. 13. Left phallomere, dorsal view. 14. Median sclerite, dorsal view. 15. Detail median sclerite, dorsal view. 16. Right phallomere, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226106/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,245,1555,1579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Median sclerite with strongly acute apex, markedly sclerotized, forming an arrow shape (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[249,1335,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[239,1348,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Epilampra pereirae sp. nov. Holotype ♂. 9. Head, ventral view. 10. Pronotum, dorsal view. 11. Supranal plate, dorsal view. 12. Subgenital plate, ventral view. 13. Left phallomere, dorsal view. 14. Median sclerite, dorsal view. 15. Detail median sclerite, dorsal view. 16. Right phallomere, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226106/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Figs. 
<number box="[1358,1386,1555,1579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="14.0">14</number>
and 
<number box="[151,182,1590,1615]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Right phallomere well developed, projecting pre-apically, with its apex acute and markedly bent over (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[249,1335,201,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[239,1348,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Epilampra pereirae sp. nov. Holotype ♂. 9. Head, ventral view. 10. Pronotum, dorsal view. 11. Supranal plate, dorsal view. 12. Subgenital plate, ventral view. 13. Left phallomere, dorsal view. 14. Median sclerite, dorsal view. 15. Detail median sclerite, dorsal view. 16. Right phallomere, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226106/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="490">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,1626,1651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="490" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
